    "contents": "<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" id=\"MPParagraphElement:F61DF6AB-07BD-4661-86A1-23A62E24563D\" class=\"MPElement\" data-object-type=\"MPParagraphElement\">Notes: The chart illustrates the difference between coefficient of variation in expectations of months to return to normal sales for the sample of SMEs and Large Firms in each country. The values of coefficients for Zambia were 2.97 and 1.91 for Large firms and SMEs respectively, outside the range of the illustration. Stratification weights adjusted for the follow-up enterprise surveys according to median eligibility were used to produce the estimates. The weights account for non-response, assuming that businesses that could not be re-contacted (unobtainable) have exited the market</p>",
