  },
  {
    "priority": 7,
    "title": "SME responses and resilience strategies are different from those of large firms",
    "label": "3",
    "path": ["MPSection:0743984D-41C6-490A-A9C9-C8D7C09E5206"],
    "elementIDs": [
      "MPParagraphElement:0001AF24-397A-42C3-B347-7CD4C6F072DF",
      "MPParagraphElement:D2361CB8-4456-45B9-95A2-C052B335F731"
    ],
    "_id": "MPSection:0743984D-41C6-490A-A9C9-C8D7C09E5206",
    "objectType": "MPSection",
    "containerID": "MPProject:B81D5F33-6338-420C-AAEC-CF0CF33E675C",
    "manuscriptID": "MPManuscript:9E0BEDBC-1084-4AA1-AB82-10ACFAE02232"
  },
  {
    "elementType": "p",
    "contents": "<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" id=\"MPParagraphElement:0001AF24-397A-42C3-B347-7CD4C6F072DF\" class=\"MPElement\" data-object-type=\"MPParagraphElement\">There is substantial variation in how SMEs respond to the crisis, both within the segment and compared to their large counterparts. While cross-country differences play a role, with SMEs in countries like Italy and Greece much more likely to be operating in affected sectors, structural differences between SMEs and large firms explain much of these variations (<span class=\"citation\" data-reference-id=\"MPCitation:E6996C0C-A8FE-4CF8-9543-43560C00F51C\">OECD, 2020b</span>). These differences could be due to expectations on the duration of shutdown affecting the type and magnitude of firm response to the crisis (see <span class=\"citation\" data-reference-id=\"MPCitation:88AE27F8-42CE-42B9-B815-3A5C6AF1ED73\">Buchheim et al., 2020</span>, on German firms). In addition, the crisis reinforces any pre-existing weaknesses among firms, hence affecting their ability to cope.</p>",
    "placeholderInnerHTML": "",
    "_id": "MPParagraphElement:0001AF24-397A-42C3-B347-7CD4C6F072DF",
    "objectType": "MPParagraphElement",
    "containerID": "MPProject:B81D5F33-6338-420C-AAEC-CF0CF33E675C",
    "manuscriptID": "MPManuscript:9E0BEDBC-1084-4AA1-AB82-10ACFAE02232"
  },
  {
    "elementType": "p",
    "contents": "<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" id=\"MPParagraphElement:D2361CB8-4456-45B9-95A2-C052B335F731\" class=\"MPElement\" data-object-type=\"MPParagraphElement\">In this section we look at differences in firm responses to the COVID-19 crisis broadly classified under three categories: i.) operational; ii.) financial; and iii.) structural.</p>",
    "placeholderInnerHTML": "",
    "_id": "MPParagraphElement:D2361CB8-4456-45B9-95A2-C052B335F731",
    "objectType": "MPParagraphElement",
    "containerID": "MPProject:B81D5F33-6338-420C-AAEC-CF0CF33E675C",
    "manuscriptID": "MPManuscript:9E0BEDBC-1084-4AA1-AB82-10ACFAE02232"
  },
  {
    "priority": 8,
    "title": "SMEs forced to adopt sharp near-term operational adjustments",
    "label": "3.1",
    "path": [
      "MPSection:0743984D-41C6-490A-A9C9-C8D7C09E5206",
      "MPSection:7BCC9134-3488-4FF0-AB45-D5DCD3AAE635"
    ],
    "elementIDs": [
      "MPParagraphElement:3F91FD9A-AF95-44DD-9D57-02C120D0B99C",
      "MPParagraphElement:FAC327C5-35F2-46CF-8E90-5B0B1F236981",
      "MPFigureElement:DE530043-99A7-4378-99F6-6F7E3CD6A6EC",
      "MPParagraphElement:2C4B084C-534D-4C9A-B3E1-8B42E9908B2E",
      "MPParagraphElement:C7DAF7B8-9831-4C3C-B827-A0FCB5DEA705",
      "MPParagraphElement:E1D88BD0-8AAA-4CC6-84A4-79E58730DFAB"
    ],
    "_id": "MPSection:7BCC9134-3488-4FF0-AB45-D5DCD3AAE635",
    "objectType": "MPSection",
    "containerID": "MPProject:B81D5F33-6338-420C-AAEC-CF0CF33E675C",
    "manuscriptID": "MPManuscript:9E0BEDBC-1084-4AA1-AB82-10ACFAE02232"
  },
  {
    "elementType": "p",
    "contents": "<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" id=\"MPParagraphElement:3F91FD9A-AF95-44DD-9D57-02C120D0B99C\" class=\"MPElement\" data-object-type=\"MPParagraphElement\">Although the shares across firms of all sizes are still low, SMEs are more likely to close their operations permanently.<span class=\"footnote\" data-reference-id=\"MPFootnote:926B5A9B-AA96-4675-A929-B4E9CCD3AC20\">12</span> Consistent with this observation is that SMEs are more likely to run into financial difficulties and file for insolvency or bankruptcy.<span class=\"footnote\" data-reference-id=\"MPFootnote:1BF0ED9C-65FA-49EF-9DE8-69DCD3B80653\">13</span> It is crucial to highlight that close to none of the large firms sampled have closed permanently since the crisis began. In addition, while blanket lockdowns forced large firms to at least close temporarily,<span class=\"footnote\" data-reference-id=\"MPFootnote:77F78449-7034-4058-8F7C-8847807E02D5\">14</span> they tend to reopen earlier on average.<span class=\"footnote\" data-reference-id=\"MPFootnote:9EBA2FDD-188D-46E2-889C-1654608D3CC8\">15</span> For some poorer countries, this can be up to a month earlier.</p>",
    "placeholderInnerHTML": "",
    "_id": "MPParagraphElement:3F91FD9A-AF95-44DD-9D57-02C120D0B99C",
    "objectType": "MPParagraphElement",
    "containerID": "MPProject:B81D5F33-6338-420C-AAEC-CF0CF33E675C",
    "manuscriptID": "MPManuscript:9E0BEDBC-1084-4AA1-AB82-10ACFAE02232"
  },
  {
    "elementType": "p",
    "contents": "<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" id=\"MPParagraphElement:FAC327C5-35F2-46CF-8E90-5B0B1F236981\" class=\"MPElement\" data-object-type=\"MPParagraphElement\">Small firms are not more likely than larger firms in the same location and sector to adjust their production or services in response to the crisis (<span class=\"cross-reference\" data-reference-id=\"MPAuxiliaryObjectReference:30508597-B75A-4B1F-A01E-666373F5E27E\"><span class=\"kind elementIndex\"><b>Figure 6</b></span></span>). This could include partial adjustments in modes of production or service delivery, which can likely range from higher online interactions with customers<span class=\"footnote\" data-reference-id=\"MPFootnote:DA0D539F-BF84-41B8-8C74-32B078822E41\">16</span> and digital marketing to a gradual adoption of digital payments. As SMEs largely cater to their respective locales, they are more likely to start or increase delivery of goods, services or carry outs by 8 percentage points. <span class=\"cross-reference\" data-reference-id=\"MPAuxiliaryObjectReference:969A165A-9DBB-45F6-9CC5-19DC3B70D15F\"><span class=\"kind elementIndex\"><b>Figure A2</b></span></span> in the Annex shows this is predominantly explained by smaller firms, which are more likely to start delivery or carryout by over 9 percentage points.</p>",
    "placeholderInnerHTML": "",
    "_id": "MPParagraphElement:FAC327C5-35F2-46CF-8E90-5B0B1F236981",
    "objectType": "MPParagraphElement",
    "containerID": "MPProject:B81D5F33-6338-420C-AAEC-CF0CF33E675C",
    "manuscriptID": "MPManuscript:9E0BEDBC-1084-4AA1-AB82-10ACFAE02232"
  },
  {
    "containedObjectIDs": ["MPFigure:CC4AA7CA-77D6-40F6-AC58-04E0C1654A59"],
    "caption": "<p class=\"caption-description\" data-placeholder-text=\"Caption...\" contenteditable=\"true\">SMEs cope with the crisis differently than large firms</p>",
    "elementType": "figure",
    "listingID": "MPListing:47ADE8E3-83CE-4996-A04D-B5487157C053",
    "_id": "MPFigureElement:DE530043-99A7-4378-99F6-6F7E3CD6A6EC",
